ce but not in the knowledge file table, which isn't essential for decision-making.\n\nThe 不具合の起因バージョン column is all dashes in the source, so omitting it from the knowledge file makes sense. The コンテンツ column describing artifact types (オブジェクトコード、ソースコード / 解説書 / ブランクプロジェクト) isn't explicitly included in the knowledge file, but the information is mostly captured in the descriptions, so this is acceptable.\n\nFor the バージョンアップ手順 section, all three steps are accounted for: updating nablarch-bom to 5u25 in pom.xml, changing the Micrometer adapter library versions to 1.13.0, and re-running the Maven build.\n\nNow checking for fabrication issues—I notice the knowledge file has \"Content-Security-Politcy\" in section s1, No. 2, but the source correctly shows \"Content-Security-Policy\". This is a typo in the knowledge file that doesn't match the source.\n\nLooking at section s2, the version 1.13.0 for Step 2 is confirmed in the source. The 参照先 URLs at the bottom of s1 appear to be additions for navigation purposes, sourced from the original file. I need to verify whether No. 6 in the knowledge file correctly shows the full version information for nablarch-document.\n\nChecking No. 7 more carefully — the source describes the micrometer library upgrade impact and the need to update dependent libraries for CloudWatch or Datadog integration. The knowledge file's Important note accurately reflects this and mentions micrometer-registry-statsd, which aligns with what's in the バージョンアップ手順 section.\n\nNow examining the two main sections in the source document...\n\nthe release note table and the upgrade procedure steps map to s1 and s2 in the knowledge file, which is correct. The section IDs follow a sequential format.\n\nLooking at the hints array for s1, I notice some module names are missing — specifically \"nablarch-single-module-archetype\" appears in the source for No. 3, 4, and 6, and \"nablarch-document\" also shows up multiple times, but neither appears in the hints list. Let me 